{"title_page": "Vuyyuru", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{more citations needed|date=July 2014}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Vuyyuru\n| native_name                     = \n| native_name_lang                = te\n| other_name                      = \n| nickname                        = \n| settlement_type                 = [[Town]]\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| pushpin_map                     = India Andhra Pradesh\n| pushpin_label_position          = right\n| pushpin_map_alt                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Andhra Pradesh, India\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|16|22|0|N|80|51|0|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = [[Country]]\n| subdivision_name                = [[India]]\n| subdivision_type1               = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Andhra Pradesh]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Krishna district|Krishna]]\n| subdivision_type3               = [[List of mandals in Andhra Pradesh|Mandal]]\n| subdivision_name3               = [[Vuyyuru mandal|Vuyyuru]]\n| established_title               = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date                = \n| founder                         = \n| government_type                 = [[Municipality]]\n| governing_body                  = \n| leader_title2                   = Commissioner\n| leader_name2                    = K Siva Rami Reddy\n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| area_footnotes                  = <ref name=civicbody>{{cite web|title=Municipalities, Municipal Corporations & UDAs|url=http://dtcp.ap.gov.in:9090/webdtcp/Municipalities%20List-110.pdf|website=Directorate of Town and Country Planning|publisher=Government of Andhra Pradesh|accessdate=29 January 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160128175528/http://dtcp.ap.gov.in:9090/webdtcp/Municipalities%20List-110.pdf|archivedate=28 January 2016|format=PDF}}</ref>\n| area_rank                       = \n| area_total_km2                  = 16.84\n| elevation_footnotes             = <ref>{{cite web|title=Elevation for Vuyyuru|url=http://veloroutes.org/elevation/?location=Vuyyuru&units=m|publisher=Veloroutes|accessdate=5 August 2014}}</ref>\n| elevation_m                     = 16\n| population_total                = 46490\n| population_as_of                = 2011\n| population_rank                 = \n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| population_demonym              = \n| population_footnotes            = <ref name=population>{{cite web|title=Census 2011|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/pca/SearchDetails.aspx?Id=628106|publisher=The Registrar General & Census Commissioner, India|accessdate=23 November 2014}}</ref>\n| demographics_type1              = [[Languages]]\n| demographics1_title1            = Official\n| demographics1_info1             = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code                     = 521 165\n| area_code_type                  = [[Telephone numbers in India|Telephone code]]\n| area_code                       = +91\u201308676\n| registration_plate              = AP 16\n| blank1_name_sec1                = [[Lok Sabha]]<br>constituency\n| blank1_info_sec1                = [[Machilipatnam (Lok Sabha constituency)|Machilipatnam]]\n| blank2_name_sec1                = [[Vidhan Sabha]]<br>constituency\n| blank2_info_sec1                = [[Penamaluru (Assembly constituency)|Penamaluru]]\n| website                         = {{URL|https://vuyyuru.cdma.ap.gov.in/en/municipality-profile}}\n| footnotes                       = \n| official_name                   = \n}}\n\n'''Vuyyuru''' is a town in [[Krishna district]] of the [[India]]n state of [[Andhra Pradesh]].It is a [[Nagar panchayat]] and the headquarters of [[Vuyyuru Mandal]].<ref name=\"civicbody\" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Krishna District Mandals|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/maps/atlas/28part31.pdf |publisher=Census of India|accessdate=19 January 2015|pages=510, 530|format=PDF}}</ref><ref name=census>{{cite web|title=District Census Handbook - Krishna|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/dchb/2817_PART_B_DCHB_KRISHNA.pdf|website=Census of India|accessdate=7 February 2016|page=16,412|format=PDF}}</ref> It is emerging as neighbourhood of [[Vijayawada]], [[India]] situated 28&nbsp;km away.\n\n== History ==\n\nIt was part of [[Satavahana dynasty]] during 1st century CE. In 1000 A.D. the Cholas spread their power to Kolleru area and during that period some of them settled at this place. After that it eventually became part of [[Kakatiya dynasty]]. By the 14th Century the village grew in size and population, came under the rule of the Zamindaars of Nuzivid.\n\n== Demographics ==\n\n{{As of|2011}} [[Census of India]], the town had a population of 46,490.{{Update after|2021}} The total population constitutes 23,312 males and 23,178 females \u2014a sex ratio of 994 females per 1000 males, higher than the national average of 940 per 1000.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sex Ratio |url=http://censusindia.gov.in/2011-prov-results/indiaatglance.html |publisher=The Registrar General & Census Commissioner, India |accessdate=23 November 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140922103426/http://censusindia.gov.in/2011-prov-results/indiaatglance.html |archive-date=22 September 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> 4,332 children are in the age group of 0\u20136 years, of which 2,151 are boys and 2,181 are girls. The town's average literacy rate stands at 81.87% with 34,513 literates, significantly higher than the national average of 73.00%.<ref name=population /><ref>{{cite web|title=Chapter\u20133 (Literates and Literacy rate) |url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/PCA/PCA_Highlights/pca_highlights_file/India/Chapter-3.pdf|publisher=Registrar General and Census Commissioner of India|accessdate=29 August 2014|format=PDF}}</ref> It is 40&nbsp;km away from state capital [[Amaravati]]. Vuyyuru town, in general, has tropical climate, winters last from November to February, while summers last from March to June. The annual rainfall is 92.33&nbsp;mm, most of it received during the months of August.\n\n== Economy ==\n'''Agriculture'''\nVuyyuru's economy is based on agriculture, mainly rice and sugar cane. The land is very fertile, and irrigation canals which draw water from the [[Krishna River]] crisscross the area. The main canal in the town is Pulleru Canal. A small dam and bridge were constructed during the British period on the canal in the town in 1890. This bridge served the locals for more than a century. Until 1988 small boats used to ply in some regions to transport people across. As of now, there are 6 bridges and 1 footbridge on this canal in Vuyyuru.\n\n'''Industries'''\n\n[[K.C.P Sugar and Industries Corporation Ltd]] is the first sugar manufacturing unit set up at Vuyyuru in 1941 and is one of the leading sugar manufacturing companies in India. The company has two sugar factories located in Krishna District Andra Pradesh having an aggregate crushing capacity of 11,500 tons per day. Its allied business consists of manufacturing and marketing of Rectified Spirit, Extra Neutral Alcohol, Ethanol, Organic Manure, Mycorrhiza Vam, Calcium Lactate and CO2.<ref>{{cite web|title=Info on KCP|url=http://www.kcpsugar.com/about-us.html|publisher=kcpsugar|accessdate=30 April 2015}}</ref> KCP has a [[cogeneration plant]] which produces 15 MW of power per day.<ref>{{cite web|title=Energy|url=http://www.kcpsugar.com/energy.html|publisher=kcpsugar|accessdate=30 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Governance ==\n\n'''Civic administration'''\n\nVuyyuru Municipality is the civic administrative body of the town which was constituted in the year 2011. It comes under [[Nuzvid revenue division]]. It is spread over an area of {{convert|16.84|km2|mi2|abbr=on}}.<ref name=civicbody /> The municipal chairman of Vuyyuru Nagar Panchayat is ''Khuddoos''.<ref>{{cite news|title=YSR Congress Claims Three Civic Chief Posts in Krishna|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/andhra_pradesh/YSR-Congress-Claims-Three-Civic-Chief-Posts-in-Krishna/2014/07/04/article2313847.ece|accessdate=17 July 2015|work=The New Indian Express|date=4 July 2014|location=Machilipatnam}}</ref> It is part of [[Andhra Pradesh Capital Region]] and represents East Zone(Vuyyuru Zone) divided by [[Andhra Pradesh Capital Region Development Authority]]\n\n'''Healthcare'''\n\nThe Government General Hospital is located in Katuru Road. There are two charity-funded hospitals. The [[CBM Bethel Hospital]] was established during British rule. The Rotary Eye Hospital is funded by KCP sugar factory and local residents.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://rotaryeyecarevyr.org|title=Rotary Community Service Trust |work=rotaryeyecarevyr.org}}</ref> There are several private hospitals with facilities varying from basic amenities to surgery facilities. Right now Vuyyuru is the medical center for the neighboring villages.\n\n'''Law and Order'''\n\nVuyyuru falls under [[Vijayawada City Police|Vijayawada Police Commissionerate]] and has two police stations, town and rural. The police supremo is Circle Inspector followed by Sub-Inspector functioning in the town and villages of Mandal. Vuyyuru also has a Crime Branch Police Station.\n\n'''Politics'''\n\nPreviously, Vuyyuru was an assembly constituency. But after the 2009 reorganization, it falls under [[Penamaluru (Assembly constituency)]], which in turn represents [[Machilipatnam (Lok Sabha constituency)]] of [[Andhra Pradesh]].<ref>{{cite web|title=DELIMITATION OF PARLIAMENTARY AND ASSEMBLY  CONSTITUENCIES ORDER, 2008 |url=http://eci.nic.in/eci_main/CurrentElections/CONSOLIDATED_ORDER%20_ECI%20.pdf\n|publisher=Election Commission of India|accessdate=11 October 2014|page=21,31|format=pdf}}</ref> The present [[Member of Legislative Assembly (India)|MLA]] representing [[Penamaluru (Assembly constituency)]] is [[Kolusu Parthasarathy]] and [[Member of parliament, Lok Sabha|MP]] representing [[Machilipatnam (Lok Sabha constituency)]] is [[Vallabhaneni Balasouri]] both belonging to [[YSR Congress Party]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Member's Report|url=http://www.aplegislature.org/web/legislative-assembly/member-s-information|website=Andhra Pradesh Legislature Assembly|accessdate=12 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Tenali Assembly 2014 Election Results|url=http://www.elections.in/andhra-pradesh/assembly-constituencies/penamaluru.html|publisher=Elections.in|accessdate=13 October 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Transport ==\n\n'''Roadways'''\n\nIt is located on the [[National Highway 65 (India)|National Highway 65]]. A four-lane road from Vijayawada to Machilipatnam passes through Vuyyuru.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vijayawada-Machilipatnam|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/vijayawada/2018/feb/05/vijayawada-machilipatnam-national-highway-expansion-works-gain-steam-1768428.html|website=New Indian Express|accessdate=5 February 2018}}</ref> [[APSRTC]] operates buses from Vuyyuru bus station which also has a [[Bus garage|bus depot]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Bus Stations in Districts|url=http://www.apsrtc.gov.in/Bus%20Stations.aspx|website=Andhra Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation|accessdate=8 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Sujatha Varma|first1=P|title=RTC offers a \u2018sweet\u2019 journey|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/rtc-offers-a-sweet-journey/article8204492.ece|accessdate=8 March 2016|work=The Hindu|date=7 February 2016|location=Vijayawada}}</ref> The government-owned bus stand and bus depot were constructed in 1987. The then chief minister of the state [[N. T. Rama Rao]] laid the foundation stone for the project. The town has a total road length of {{Convert|64.14|km|mi|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{cite web|title=Details of Roads in Each ULB of Andhra Pradesh|url=http://centralapp.cdma.ap.gov.in:8080/CDMAAPTaxesInfo/RoadDetails.jsp|website=Commissioner and Directorate of Municipal Administration|publisher=Municipal Administration and Urban Developmemt Department - Government of Andhra Pradesh|accessdate=28 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160801101300/http://centralapp.cdma.ap.gov.in:8080/CDMAAPTaxesInfo/RoadDetails.jsp|archive-date=1 August 2016|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> A bypass road was constructed in 1987 to divert traffic from main roads. This bypass connects Machilipatnam with Vijayawada, Hyderabad, and Pune. All heavy vehicles travel over this road to ease traffic through town. It is now developed and transformed into four-lane road and maintained by [[National Highways Authority of India|NHAI]] as [[National Highway 65 (India)|Machilipatnam-Pune Highway]].\n\nThe most common buses from Vijayawada to Vuyyuru & vice versa is 222 as well. Vijayawada railway station to pammaru via vuyyuru & vice versa is 333.\n\n'''Railways'''\n\nThere is no railway station in Vuyyuru. The nearby railway stations are [[Gudivada Junction railway station]] (22.9&nbsp;km) and [[Vijayawada Junction railway station]] (31.4&nbsp;km).\n\n'''Airways'''\n\nThe nearest airport is [[Vijayawada Airport]] which is at a distance of 24.5&nbsp;km.\n\n== Education ==\n\nVuyyuru is a center for Primary and Secondary School Education for people in surrounding villages. List of schools in Vuyyuru includes Zilla Parishat High School, VRKM High School, Sri Viswasanthi Educational Institutions, Sri Srinivasa Educational institutions (KG to PG), Flora EM High School, Ravindra Bharathi School. In terms of Intermediate colleges, there are Sri Viswasanthi junior college,Nayarayana, Chaitanya, Krishnaveni. Vuyyuru has many colleges for higher education including A.G & S.G Siddhartha Degree College of Arts and Science which was inaugurated on 12 August 1975 by then Chief Minister Sri [[Jalagam Vengala Rao]]. It is an accredited \"A\" grade by [[National Assessment and Accreditation Council|NAAC]]. The college has an indoor stadium and huge ground which serves for walkers and joggers in the town.\n\n==Sugarcane Research ==\n\nSugarcane Research Station is located in Vuyyuru which was established in 1978 in an area of 40 acres with the mandate to develop sugarcane varieties possessing high cane and sugar yield potential. It is maintained by [[Indian Institute of Sugarcane Research]] and is affiliated to [[Acharya N. G. Ranga Agricultural University|ANGRAU]]. It works on All India Coordinated Research Project on Sugarcane and has many achievements in sugarcane research.\n\n== Culture ==\nVuyyuru is famous for its temple fair ''Veeramma Thalli Thirunaallu'' which is conducted annually in February. It starts on the day of auspicious Bhishma Ekadasi. It was started in the 16th Century during the [[Vijayanagara Empire]]. It has been continued and the fair has become a famous event for hundreds of villages and acts as an agent of social and cultural cohesion. People from the town and surrounding villages celebrate this fair in various forms of traditional Indian celebrations like ''Sambaram, Jathara'' for 15 days.\n\n== Religious Places ==\n\n'''Temples'''\n\nThere are two temples under the management of Endowments Department.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tms.ap.gov.in/binfo|title=Trust Boards Abstract|last=|first=|date=|website=AP Temples Portal, Government of Andhra Pradesh|access-date=24 July 2018}}</ref> Sri Jagadambha Sametha Mallikarjuna Swamy Temple (''Shivalayam'') in the town is constructed during 13th century by [[Kakatiya dynasty|Kakatiya's]]. List of temples in the town:\n\n# Sri Jagadambha Sametha Mallikarjuna Swamy Temple (Shivalayam)\n# Sri Venugopala Swamy Temple\n# Sri Parupudi Veeramma Thalli Temple\n# Sri Abhaya Anjaneya Temple\n# Datta Digambara Kshetra\n# Kalyana Venkateswara Swami Temple\n# Sai Baba Temple\n\n'''Mosque'''\n\nAn mosque which was constructed nearly 300 years ago is located on the main road of Vuyyuru. Recently the mosque was renovated.\n\n'''Churches'''\n\nThere are many churches in Vuyyuru. CBM (Canadian Baptist Mission) church, which was constructed prior to independence, is the oldest church in the town.\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Vuyyuru mandal|Vuyyuru Mandal]]\n*[[List of villages in Krishna district#V|Villages in Vuyyuru mandal]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Krishna district}}\n{{Mandal headquarters in Krishna district}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in Krishna district]]\n[[Category:Mandal headquarters in Krishna district]]\n[[Category:Towns in Andhra Pradesh Capital Region]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{more citations needed|date=July 2014}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Vuyyuru\n| native_name                     = \n| native_name_lang                = te\n| other_name                      = \n| nickname                        = \n| settlement_type                 = [[Town]]\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| pushpin_map                     = India Andhra Pradesh\n| pushpin_label_position          = right\n| pushpin_map_alt                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Andhra Pradesh, India\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|16|22|0|N|80|51|0|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = [[Country]]\n| subdivision_name                = [[India]]\n| subdivision_type1               = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Andhra Pradesh]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Krishna district|Krishna]]\n| subdivision_type3               = [[List of mandals in Andhra Pradesh|Mandal]]\n| subdivision_name3               = [[Vuyyuru mandal|Vuyyuru]]\n| established_title               = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date                = \n| founder                         = \n| government_type                 = [[Municipality]]\n| governing_body                  = \n| leader_title2                   = Commissioner\n| leader_name2                    = K Siva Rami Reddy\n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| area_footnotes                  = <ref name=civicbody>{{cite web|title=Municipalities, Municipal Corporations & UDAs|url=http://dtcp.ap.gov.in:9090/webdtcp/Municipalities%20List-110.pdf|website=Directorate of Town and Country Planning|publisher=Government of Andhra Pradesh|accessdate=29 January 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160128175528/http://dtcp.ap.gov.in:9090/webdtcp/Municipalities%20List-110.pdf|archivedate=28 January 2016|format=PDF}}</ref>\n| area_rank                       = \n| area_total_km2                  = 16.84\n| elevation_footnotes             = <ref>{{cite web|title=Elevation for Vuyyuru|url=http://veloroutes.org/elevation/?location=Vuyyuru&units=m|publisher=Veloroutes|accessdate=5 August 2014}}</ref>\n| elevation_m                     = 16\n| population_total                = 46490\n| population_as_of                = 2011\n| population_rank                 = \n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| population_demonym              = \n| population_footnotes            = <ref name=population>{{cite web|title=Census 2011|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/pca/SearchDetails.aspx?Id=628106|publisher=The Registrar General & Census Commissioner, India|accessdate=23 November 2014}}</ref>\n| demographics_type1              = [[Languages]]\n| demographics1_title1            = Official\n| demographics1_info1             = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code                     = 521 165\n| area_code_type                  = [[Telephone numbers in India|Telephone code]]\n| area_code                       = +91\u201308676\n| registration_plate              = AP 16\n| blank1_name_sec1                = [[Lok Sabha]]<br>constituency\n| blank1_info_sec1                = [[Machilipatnam (Lok Sabha constituency)|Machilipatnam]]\n| blank2_name_sec1                = [[Vidhan Sabha]]<br>constituency\n| blank2_info_sec1                = [[Penamaluru (Assembly constituency)|Penamaluru]]\n| website                         = {{URL|https://vuyyuru.cdma.ap.gov.in/en/municipality-profile}}\n| footnotes                       = \n| official_name                   = \n}}\n\n'''Vuyyuru''' is a town in [[Krishna district]] of the [[India]]n state of [[Andhra Pradesh]].It is a [[Nagar panchayat]] and the headquarters of [[Vuyyuru Mandal]].<ref name=\"civicbody\" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Krishna District Mandals|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/maps/atlas/28part31.pdf |publisher=Census of India|accessdate=19 January 2015|pages=510, 530|format=PDF}}</ref><ref name=census>{{cite web|title=District Census Handbook - Krishna|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/dchb/2817_PART_B_DCHB_KRISHNA.pdf|website=Census of India|accessdate=7 February 2016|page=16,412|format=PDF}}</ref> It is emerging as neighbourhood of [[Vijayawada]], [[India]] situated 28&nbsp;km away.\n\n== History ==\n\nIt was part of [[Satavahana dynasty]] during 1st century CE. In 1000 A.D. the Cholas spread their power to Kolleru area and during that period some of them settled at this place. After that it eventually became part of [[Kakatiya dynasty]]. By the 14th Century the village grew in size and population, came under the rule of the Zamindaars of Nuzivid.\n\n== Demographics ==\n\n{{As of|2011}} [[Census of India]], the town had a population of 46,490.{{Update after|2021}} The total population constitutes 23,312 males and 23,178 females \u2014a sex ratio of 994 females per 1000 males, higher than the national average of 940 per 1000.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sex Ratio |url=http://censusindia.gov.in/2011-prov-results/indiaatglance.html |publisher=The Registrar General & Census Commissioner, India |accessdate=23 November 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140922103426/http://censusindia.gov.in/2011-prov-results/indiaatglance.html |archive-date=22 September 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> 4,332 children are in the age group of 0\u20136 years, of which 2,151 are boys and 2,181 are girls. The town's average literacy rate stands at 81.87% with 34,513 literates, significantly higher than the national average of 73.00%.<ref name=population /><ref>{{cite web|title=Chapter\u20133 (Literates and Literacy rate) |url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/PCA/PCA_Highlights/pca_highlights_file/India/Chapter-3.pdf|publisher=Registrar General and Census Commissioner of India|accessdate=29 August 2014|format=PDF}}</ref> It is 40&nbsp;km away from state capital [[Amaravati]]. Vuyyuru town, in general, has tropical climate, winters last from November to February, while summers last from March to June. The annual rainfall is 92.33&nbsp;mm, most of it received during the months of August.\n\n== Economy ==\n'''Agriculture'''\nVuyyuru's economy is based on agriculture, mainly rice and sugar cane. The land is very fertile, and irrigation canals which draw water from the [[Krishna River]] crisscross the area. The main canal in the town is Pulleru Canal. A small dam and bridge were constructed during the British period on the canal in the town in 1890. This bridge served the locals for more than a century. Until 1988 small boats used to ply in some regions to transport people across. As of now, there are 6 bridges and 1 footbridge on this canal in Vuyyuru.\n\n'''Industries'''\n\n[[K.C.P Sugar and Industries Corporation Ltd]] is the first sugar manufacturing unit set up at Vuyyuru in 1941 and is one of the leading sugar manufacturing companies in India. The company has two sugar factories located in Krishna District Andra Pradesh having an aggregate crushing capacity of 11,500 tons per day. Its allied business consists of manufacturing and marketing of Rectified Spirit, Extra Neutral Alcohol, Ethanol, Organic Manure, Mycorrhiza Vam, Calcium Lactate and CO2.<ref>{{cite web|title=Info on KCP|url=http://www.kcpsugar.com/about-us.html|publisher=kcpsugar|accessdate=30 April 2015}}</ref> KCP has a [[cogeneration plant]] which produces 15 MW of power per day.<ref>{{cite web|title=Energy|url=http://www.kcpsugar.com/energy.html|publisher=kcpsugar|accessdate=30 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Governance ==\n\n'''Civic administration'''\n\nVuyyuru Municipality is the civic administrative body of the town which was constituted in the year 2011. It comes under [[Nuzvid revenue division]]. It is spread over an area of {{convert|16.84|km2|mi2|abbr=on}}.<ref name=civicbody /> The municipal chairman of Vuyyuru Nagar Panchayat is ''Khuddoos''.<ref>{{cite news|title=YSR Congress Claims Three Civic Chief Posts in Krishna|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/andhra_pradesh/YSR-Congress-Claims-Three-Civic-Chief-Posts-in-Krishna/2014/07/04/article2313847.ece|accessdate=17 July 2015|work=The New Indian Express|date=4 July 2014|location=Machilipatnam}}</ref> It is part of [[Andhra Pradesh Capital Region]] and represents East Zone(Vuyyuru Zone) divided by [[Andhra Pradesh Capital Region Development Authority]]\n\n'''Healthcare'''\n\nThe Government General Hospital is located in Katuru Road. There are two charity-funded hospitals. The [[CBM Bethel Hospital]] was established during British rule. The Rotary Eye Hospital is funded by KCP sugar factory and local residents.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://rotaryeyecarevyr.org|title=Rotary Community Service Trust |work=rotaryeyecarevyr.org}}</ref> There are several private hospitals with facilities varying from basic amenities to surgery facilities. Right now Vuyyuru is the medical center for the neighboring villages.\n\n'''Law and Order'''\n\nVuyyuru falls under [[Vijayawada City Police|Vijayawada Police Commissionerate]] and has two police stations, town and rural. The police supremo is Circle Inspector followed by Sub-Inspector functioning in the town and villages of Mandal. Vuyyuru also has a Crime Branch Police Station.\n\n'''Politics'''\n\nPreviously, Vuyyuru was an assembly constituency. But after the 2009 reorganization, it falls under [[Penamaluru (Assembly constituency)]], which in turn represents [[Machilipatnam (Lok Sabha constituency)]] of [[Andhra Pradesh]].<ref>{{cite web|title=DELIMITATION OF PARLIAMENTARY AND ASSEMBLY  CONSTITUENCIES ORDER, 2008 |url=http://eci.nic.in/eci_main/CurrentElections/CONSOLIDATED_ORDER%20_ECI%20.pdf\n|publisher=Election Commission of India|accessdate=11 October 2014|page=21,31|format=pdf}}</ref> The present [[Member of Legislative Assembly (India)|MLA]] representing [[Penamaluru (Assembly constituency)]] is [[Kolusu Parthasarathy]] and [[Member of parliament, Lok Sabha|MP]] representing [[Machilipatnam (Lok Sabha constituency)]] is [[Vallabhaneni Balasouri]] both belonging to [[YSR Congress Party]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Member's Report|url=http://www.aplegislature.org/web/legislative-assembly/member-s-information|website=Andhra Pradesh Legislature Assembly|accessdate=12 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Tenali Assembly 2014 Election Results|url=http://www.elections.in/andhra-pradesh/assembly-constituencies/penamaluru.html|publisher=Elections.in|accessdate=13 October 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Transport ==\n\n'''Roadways'''\n\nIt is located on the [[National Highway 65 (India)|National Highway 65]]. A four-lane road from Vijayawada to Machilipatnam passes through Vuyyuru.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vijayawada-Machilipatnam|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/vijayawada/2018/feb/05/vijayawada-machilipatnam-national-highway-expansion-works-gain-steam-1768428.html|website=New Indian Express|accessdate=5 February 2018}}</ref> [[APSRTC]] operates buses from Vuyyuru bus station which also has a [[Bus garage|bus depot]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Bus Stations in Districts|url=http://www.apsrtc.gov.in/Bus%20Stations.aspx|website=Andhra Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation|accessdate=8 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Sujatha Varma|first1=P|title=RTC offers a \u2018sweet\u2019 journey|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/rtc-offers-a-sweet-journey/article8204492.ece|accessdate=8 March 2016|work=The Hindu|date=7 February 2016|location=Vijayawada}}</ref> The government-owned bus stand and bus depot were constructed in 1987. The then chief minister of the state [[N. T. Rama Rao]] laid the foundation stone for the project. The town has a total road length of {{Convert|64.14|km|mi|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{cite web|title=Details of Roads in Each ULB of Andhra Pradesh|url=http://centralapp.cdma.ap.gov.in:8080/CDMAAPTaxesInfo/RoadDetails.jsp|website=Commissioner and Directorate of Municipal Administration|publisher=Municipal Administration and Urban Developmemt Department - Government of Andhra Pradesh|accessdate=28 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160801101300/http://centralapp.cdma.ap.gov.in:8080/CDMAAPTaxesInfo/RoadDetails.jsp|archive-date=1 August 2016|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> A bypass road was constructed in 1987 to divert traffic from main roads. This bypass connects Machilipatnam with Vijayawada, Hyderabad, and Pune. All heavy vehicles travel over this road to ease traffic through town. It is now developed and transformed into four-lane road and maintained by [[National Highways Authority of India|NHAI]] as [[National Highway 65 (India)|Machilipatnam-Pune Highway]].\n\nThe most common buses from Vijayawada to Vuyyuru & vice versa is 222 as well. Vijayawada railway station to pammaru via vuyyuru & vice versa is 333.\n\n'''Railways'''\n\nThere is no railway station in Vuyyuru. The nearby railway stations are [[Gudivada Junction railway station]] (22.9&nbsp;km) and [[Vijayawada Junction railway station]] (31.4&nbsp;km).\n\n'''Airways'''\n\nThe nearest airport is [[Vijayawada Airport]] which is at a distance of 24.5&nbsp;km.\n\n== Education ==\n\nVuyyuru is a center for Primary and Secondary School Education for people in surrounding villages. List of schools in Vuyyuru includes Zilla Parishat High School, VRKM High School, Sri Viswasanthi Educational Institutions, Sri Srinivasa Educational institutions (KG to PG), Flora EM High School, Ravindra Bharathi School. In terms of Intermediate colleges, there were Nayarayana, Chaitanya, Krishnaveni. Vuyyuru has many colleges for higher education including A.G & S.G Siddhartha Degree College of Arts and Science which was inaugurated on 12 August 1975 by then Chief Minister Sri [[Jalagam Vengala Rao]]. It is an accredited \"A\" grade by [[National Assessment and Accreditation Council|NAAC]]. The college has an indoor stadium and huge ground which serves for walkers and joggers in the town.\n\n==Sugarcane Research ==\n\nSugarcane Research Station is located in Vuyyuru which was established in 1978 in an area of 40 acres with the mandate to develop sugarcane varieties possessing high cane and sugar yield potential. It is maintained by [[Indian Institute of Sugarcane Research]] and is affiliated to [[Acharya N. G. Ranga Agricultural University|ANGRAU]]. It works on All India Coordinated Research Project on Sugarcane and has many achievements in sugarcane research.\n\n== Culture ==\nVuyyuru is famous for its temple fair ''Veeramma Thalli Thirunaallu'' which is conducted annually in February. It starts on the day of auspicious Bhishma Ekadasi. It was started in the 16th Century during the [[Vijayanagara Empire]]. It has been continued and the fair has become a famous event for hundreds of villages and acts as an agent of social and cultural cohesion. People from the town and surrounding villages celebrate this fair in various forms of traditional Indian celebrations like ''Sambaram, Jathara'' for 15 days.\n\n== Religious Places ==\n\n'''Temples'''\n\nThere are two temples under the management of Endowments Department.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tms.ap.gov.in/binfo|title=Trust Boards Abstract|last=|first=|date=|website=AP Temples Portal, Government of Andhra Pradesh|access-date=24 July 2018}}</ref> Sri Jagadambha Sametha Mallikarjuna Swamy Temple (''Shivalayam'') in the town is constructed during 13th century by [[Kakatiya dynasty|Kakatiya's]]. List of temples in the town:\n\n# Sri Jagadambha Sametha Mallikarjuna Swamy Temple (Shivalayam)\n# Sri Venugopala Swamy Temple\n# Sri Parupudi Veeramma Thalli Temple\n# Sri Abhaya Anjaneya Temple\n# Datta Digambara Kshetra\n# Kalyana Venkateswara Swami Temple\n# Sai Baba Temple\n\n'''Mosque'''\n\nAn mosque which was constructed nearly 300 years ago is located on the main road of Vuyyuru. Recently the mosque was renovated.\n\n'''Churches'''\n\nThere are many churches in Vuyyuru. CBM (Canadian Baptist Mission) church, which was constructed prior to independence, is the oldest church in the town.\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Vuyyuru mandal|Vuyyuru Mandal]]\n*[[List of villages in Krishna district#V|Villages in Vuyyuru mandal]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Krishna district}}\n{{Mandal headquarters in Krishna district}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in Krishna district]]\n[[Category:Mandal headquarters in Krishna district]]\n[[Category:Towns in Andhra Pradesh Capital Region]]\n", "name_user": "Surya Madala", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eEducation:Added content)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vuyyuru"}
{"title_page": "Lilly Singh", "text_new": "{{Short description|Canadian YouTuber, comedian, talk show host, and actress}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name            = Lilly Singh\n| image           = File:Lilly Singh by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| caption         = Singh speaking at [[Vidcon]] in 2014\n| birth_name      =\n| alias           = IISuperwomanII\n| birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1988|09|26}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iKeOljPdshk|title=Why Bathrooms Are Stressful!|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n| birth_place     = [[Scarborough, Toronto|Scarborough, Ontario]], Canada\n| nationality     = [[Canadians|Canadian]]\n| education       = [[York University]]\n| residence       = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.\n| occupation      = {{flatlist|\n* Television host\n* [[YouTuber]]\n* [[actress]]\n* writer}}\n|height           = {{height|ft=5|in=5|out=cm}}<ref>{{Citation|last=IISuperwomanII|title=50 Random Things About Me|date=August 6, 2013|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nrXdEoUl2Q8&t=158|accessdate=February 26, 2017}}</ref>\n| website         = {{URL|www.lillysingh.com}}\n| years active    = 2010\u2013present\n| module          = {{Infobox YouTube personality|embed=yes\n| channel_name    = Lilly\n| genre           = {{flatlist|\n* [[Comedy]]\n* [[vlog]]s\n* [[Sketch comedy|skits]]\n* [[Diatribe|rants]]\n* [[Motivational speaker|motivation]]\n}}\n| network         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Studio 71]]\n* Sarah Weichel Management}}\n| gold_year       = 2013\n| diamond_year    = 2016\n| silver_button   = yes\n| gold_button     = yes\n| diamond_button  = yes\n}}\n}}\n'''Lilly Singh''' (born September 26, 1988) is a Canadian [[YouTuber]], comedian, talk show host, writer, and actress, who initially gained fame on social media under the [[pseudonym]] '''IISuperwomanII'''. Born and raised in [[Scarborough, Toronto|Scarborough]], [[Ontario]], Singh began making [[YouTube]] videos in 2010. By 2017, she was ranked tenth on the ''[[Forbes]]'' list of the world's highest paid YouTube stars, earning a reported [[United States dollar|$]]10.5 million; as of September 2019 she has fourteen million subscribers, and over three billion video views.<ref>{{cite news|title=The World's Highest-Paid YouTube Stars 2017: 10. Lilly Singh| url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/5a275d6931358e286471a7e8/10-lilly-singh/| accessdate=February 26, 2018|work=Forbes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/how-lilly-singh-is-making-late-night-tv-history|title=How Lilly Singh is making late-night TV history|last=Wakeam|first=Kira|date=September 16, 2019|website=[[PBS NewsHour]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=December 27, 2019}}</ref> Singh has featured in the annual [[YouTube Rewind]] every year since 2014.<ref>{{cite web| author1=Mangala Dilip|title=Watch YouTube Rewind: Turn Down for 2014 Video Looks Back on Viral Trends, People, Music of Last Year|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/watch-youtube-rewind-turn-down-2014-video-looks-back-viral-trends-people-music-last-year-616717#wIyPvwj7jDchjYjw.97|website=International Business Times|accessdate=July 23, 2016|date=December 10, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author1=Casey Lewis| title=YouTube's 2015 Year in Rewind Video Will Make the Last 365 Days Flash Before Your Eyes|url=http://www.teenvogue.com/story/youtubes-2015-rewind-video-cameron-dallas-lilly-singh|website=Teen Vogue| publisher=Cond\u00e9 Nast Digital|accessdate=July 23, 2016|date=December 10, 2015}}</ref> ''[[Forbes]]'' named her one of the 40 most powerful people in comedy in 2019.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=O'Connor| first1=Clare| title=Forbes Top Influencers: How YouTuber Lilly Singh Is Going Mainstream \u2013 And Making Millions|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/clareoconnor/2017/06/20/forbes-top-influencers-lilly-singh-superwoman-youtube/#1cea120e33e7| magazine=[[Forbes.com]]|date=June 20, 2017}}</ref> Singh has received an [[MTV Fandom Awards|MTV Fandom Award]], four [[Streamy Awards]], two [[Teen Choice Awards]], and a [[People's Choice Award]].\n\nIn 2016, Singh released her first film, a [[Documentary film|documentary]] chronicling her world tour, entitled ''[[A Trip to Unicorn Island]]''. In March 2017, she released her first book, ''How to Be a Bawse: A Guide to Conquering Life'', which reached number one on the [[New York Times Best Seller|''New York Times'' best-seller]] list. Since September 2019, Singh acts as executive producer and host of the [[NBC]] [[late-night talk show]], ''[[A Little Late with Lilly Singh]]''.<ref>{{cite news |title=YouTube star Lilly Singh to launch a late night talk show on NBC |url=https://filmindustry.network/youtube-star-lilly-singh-to-launch-a-late-night-talk-show-on-nbc/34392 |publisher=Film Industry Network |date=March 15, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/03/15/business/media/lilly-singh-carson-daly-nbc.html|title=Lilly Singh, a YouTube Star, Will Host a Late-Night Show on NBC|last=Le\u00f3n|first=Concepci\u00f3n de|date=March 15, 2019|work=The New York Times|access-date=March 17, 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Singh is the only openly [[LGBT|LGBTQ]]+ person\u2014being [[Bisexuality|bisexual]]\u2014as well as the first person of Indian descent, hosting an American major broadcast network late-night talk show.{{Efn|[[Wanda Sykes]], an out lesbian comic, hosted a season of her own show.|name=|group=}}<ref name=\"first\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/feature/nbc-out/youtube-star-lilly-singh-set-become-first-bisexual-late-night-n983896|title=YouTube star Lilly Singh set to become first bisexual late-night host|website=NBC News|language=en|access-date=2019-03-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/entertainment/singh-talk-show-1.5280121|title='All these people have my back:' celebs support Lilly Singh's talk show debut|last=|first=|date=Sep 11, 2019|website=[[CBC News]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://rollingstoneindia.com/lilly-singh-late-night-show/|title=YouTube Star Lilly Singh is the First Woman of Indian-Origin to Host a U.S. Late Night Show -|last=|first=|date=March 16, 2019|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] India|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=October 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nSingh was born and raised in the [[Scarborough, Toronto|Scarborough]] district of [[Toronto|Toronto, Ontario]]. Her parents, Malwinder Kaur and Sukhwinder Singh,<ref>{{cite web |author=nurun.com |url=http://www.toronto24hours.ca/2016/02/18/lilly-singh-is-truly-superwoman |title=Lilly Singh is truly Superwoman &#124; 24 Hours Toronto |publisher=Toronto24hours.ca |date=February 18, 2016 |accessdate=April 7, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170819022510/http://www.toronto24hours.ca/2016/02/18/lilly-singh-is-truly-superwoman |archive-date=August 19, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> emigrated from [[Hoshiarpur]], [[Punjab, India|Punjab]], [[India]], and raised her as a [[Sikh]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.biography.com/personality/lilly-singh|title=Lilly Singh|website=Biography}}</ref> She has an older sister named Tina Singh (born 1982), who is also a YouTuber who makes videos about her family life with her husband and three boys.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC5cdO1UKWYO_k0evsXohIIA|title=Neurotic Mom Diaries|publisher=Tina's Youtube channel| website=YouTube|note=|access-date=May 12, 2016}}</ref> As a child, Singh has said she was a [[tomboy]].<ref>{{cite news|title=How three local comics found global fame| url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/toronto/how-three-local-comics-found-global-fame/article4107501/| accessdate=July 2, 2014|work=[[The Globe and Mail]]|date=April 13, 2012}}</ref> She attended Mary Shadd Public School during her elementary years, and in 2006, she graduated from [[Lester B. Pearson Collegiate Institute]] in [[Toronto]], where she returned as an alumna to visit her old teachers.<ref>{{cite news| last=Persaud| first=Devin|title=My Roots- Outstanding Student of the Season| url=http://www.my-roots.ca/cms/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/SUMMER-2008-MY-ROOTS.pdf| work=My Roots|accessdate=November 5, 2014}}</ref> She was a member of [[Girl Guides of Canada]] and participated in their youth programs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/i/web/status/1100116560050565120|title=Lilly Singh AKA Superwoman (and former Girl Guide!) is showing everyone that she can be #everythingshewantstobe by simply being herself! Thank you for inspiring others to accept and unleash their own superpowers. |publisher=Girl Guides of Canada|date=February 25, 2019|website=Twitter|language=en|access-date=March 14, 2019}}</ref> In 2010, she graduated from [[York University]] in Toronto with a [[Bachelor of Arts]] in Psychology.<ref>{{cite web|title='Superwoman' Lilly Singh: From York grad to international YouTube star| url=http://advancement.yorku.ca/2015/01/18/lilly-singh-lol/| publisher=[[York University]]|accessdate=February 24, 2018|date=January 18, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/tv/youtuber-lilly-singh-comes-out-bisexual/|title=Youtuber Lilly Singh Comes Out as Bisexual: These Are My 'Superpowers'|last=Guglielmi|first=Jodi|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=February 25, 2019|accessdate=June 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===Creating YouTube channel and rise to popularity (2010\u20132014)===\nIn October 2010, Singh started a YouTube channel under the pseudonym \"IISuperwomanII\". She has explained that the name ''Superwoman'' was prompted by a childhood idea, making her believe she could do anything. Starting out, Singh had intended to go to graduate school as her parents had requested, but chose to make YouTube videos and decided that she would return to graduate school if her YouTube career did not succeed.\n\nIn December 2011, Singh created a second channel called SuperwomanVlogs, now titled Lilly Singh Vlogs, where she chronicles her daily activities and includes behind the scenes footage from her videos. She used it as a second channel to upload videos until August 2014, when she began uploading daily vlogs. Originally uploading daily, she now uploads several times a week. Singh appeared as a background dancer in the movies ''[[Speedy Singhs (2011 film)|Speedy Singhs]]'' and ''[[Thank You (2011 film)|Thank You]]'' in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/music/urban/12077-interview-iisuperwomanii|title=INTERVIEW: IISUPERWOMANII|last=Khan|first=Maz|publisher=[[MTV (UK and Ireland)|MTV]]|accessdate=June 30, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2013, Singh featured alongside [[Jassi Sidhu]] in his Punjabi song ''Hipshaker''. Singh [[Rapping|rapped]] in the song ''Mauj Ki Malharein'', which played in the [[Bollywood]] drama ''[[Gulaab Gang]]'' in August 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/more/videos/view/id/2427757|title=Mauj Ki Malharein (Gulaab Gang)|work=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|accessdate=November 5, 2014}}</ref> In July of the same year, she released a song titled ''#LEH'' in a collaboration with her friend, author and rapper [[Kanwer Singh]], who is known by the pseudonym \"Humble the Poet\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/punjabi/music/LEH--Superwoman-Humble-The-Poet-video-out-now/articleshow/37621828.cms|title=#LEH \u2013 Superwoman & Humble The Poet video out now|date=July 2, 2014|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=July 2, 2014}}</ref> In 2014, Singh appeared in a small role in the Canadian production ''[[Dr. Cabbie]]''.\n\nIn 2014, her channel ranked at #39 on [[New Media Rockstars]] Top 100 Channels.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://newmediarockstars.com/2014/12/the-nmr-top-100-youtube-channels-50-26/|title=The NMR Top 100 YouTube Channels: 50-26!|website=New Media Rockstars|accessdate=January 6, 2015}}</ref> The same year, she was nominated for a Shorty Award and a Streamy Award.\n\n===World tour, move to Los Angeles, and documentary (2015\u20132016)===\nShe recorded and released another music video in February 2015 titled ''The Clean Up Anthem'' in collaboration with Canadian artist Sickick.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.browngirlmagazine.com/2015/02/lily-singh-a-k-a-superwomans-new-anthem-will-make-you-want-to-clean-your-room-literally/|title=Lily Singh a.k.a Superwoman's New Anthem Will Make you Want to Clean Your Room|publisher=Brown Girl Magazine|accessdate=February 24, 2015}}</ref> [[File: Lilly Singh.JPG|thumb|Lilly Singh (IISuperwomanII) performs at the Warfield in San Francisco during her world tour, \"A Trip to Unicorn Island\".]]\nIn March 2015, Singh began a world tour called \"A Trip to Unicorn Island\", adapting her YouTube content and including singing, dancing, music performances, comedy, and her parent characters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.torontosun.com/2015/05/15/superwoman-lilly-singh-readies-her-first-world-tour|title=Superwoman Lilly Singh readies her first world tour|work=Toronto Sun|accessdate=November 9, 2015}}</ref> Her tour covered India, Australia, Hong Kong, Singapore, Dubai, Canada, Trinidad, and Tobago, the United Kingdom, and the United States. She documented the tour in her first feature movie, ''[[A Trip to Unicorn Island]]'', which also describes how YouTube fame is affecting her life. The movie was released on February 10, 2016 on YouTube Red.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.ew.com/article/2015/07/24/lilly-singh-trip-to-unicorn-island-teaser|title=Lilly Singh: A Trip to Unicorn Isle and teaser released|work=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=November 9, 2015}}</ref> She describes the film as being very \"raw and genuine\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/02/09/lilly-singh-trip-to-unicorn-island-interview|title=Lilly Singh admits the hardest part of filming 'A Trip to Unicorn Island'|website=Entertainment Weekly|access-date=March 8, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2015, Singh released a song about her hometown Toronto in collaboration with Humble the Poet titled ''#IVIVI'' (roman numerals for 416, Toronto's area code).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2015/04/16/superwoman-humble-the-poet-ivivi_n_7083820.html|title=Superwoman And Humble The Poet Show Toronto Pride In #IVIVI Music Video|work=The Huffington Post|accessdate=April 16, 2015}}</ref>\nIn September 2015, ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'' magazine included Singh on their annual \"Ones to Watch\" list.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/gallery/0,,20952900_30388187,00.html#30388213|title=Their Stars Are Rising: Meet PEOPLE's 2015 Ones to Watch!|date=September 16, 2015|website=People.com|publisher=Time Inc.|accessdate=December 15, 2015}}</ref> Lilly received her first MTV Fandom Award, was nominated for two Teen Choice Awards, and won her first Streamy Award later that year.\n\nIn December 2015, she moved to Los Angeles to further her career.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2682337/lilly-singh-iisuperwomanii-youtube-move-los-angeles/|title=Lilly Singh's First-Ever Apartment Puts Your Place To Shame|website=MTV News|access-date=March 8, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2016, she ranked 8th on ''Forbes''{{'}} list of World's Top-Earning YouTube Stars of 2015.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/gjdm45jih/8-tie-lilly-singh-2-5-mi/|title=The World's Highest-Paid YouTube Stars 2015|last1=Berg|first1=Madeline|date=October 15, 2015|website=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=October 16, 2015}}</ref> She was also featured in Fast Company Magazine as the 100 Most Creative People in Business.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fastcompany.com/3058985/most-creative-people/lilly-singhs-road-map-for-building-a-brand-beyond-youtube|title=Lilly Singh's Road Map For Building A Brand Beyond YouTube|author=Nicole Laporte|date=May 16, 2016|website=fastcompany.com|publisher=Fast Company & Inc}}</ref> ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' magazine recognized her as one of their ''10 Comics to Watch'' for 2016, and she was honored at the [[Just For Laughs]] Film Festival in Montreal. In July 2016, she won two [[Teen Choice Awards]] from her three nominations.\n\nIn 2016, she voiced miniature unicorns named Bubbles and Misty in the animated film ''[[Ice Age: Collision Course]]'' and played a cameo role in the movie ''[[Bad Moms]]''. On August 8, 2016, Singh released a visual music piece on YouTube, titled \"Voices\". The piece includes five songs portraying the \"voices in her head\".\n\n=== Continued popularity and debut book (2017\u20132018) ===\nIn January 2017, she won a [[People's Choice Award]] for \"Favorite YouTube Star\". In September 2017, Singh won her fourth [[Streamy Award]].\n\nHer first book, ''How to Be a Bawse: A Guide to Conquering Life'', was released on March 28, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailydot.com/upstream/lilly-singh-book-deal-bawse/|title=Lilly Singh to debut first book 'How to Be a Bawse' in 2017|author1=Rae Votta|date=July 27, 2016|website=The Daily Dot|accessdate=July 27, 2016}}</ref> The book reached No. 1 on the New York Times bestseller list. Her 2017 world tour was centered around the book release and key concepts she discussed.\n\nSingh was cast in [[HBO]]'s [[Fahrenheit 451 (2018 film)|film adaptation]] of ''[[Fahrenheit 451]]'' after recording an audition outside an Internet caf\u00e9 in Melbourne, Australia. She was in the region to promote her book and rushed the audition at her agent's urging around 2 a.m. in May 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/entertainment-pmn/lilly-singh-gets-role-in-hbo-reworking-of-ray-bradburys-fahrenheit-451/wcm/dd8b063f-625e-41e9-a7b8-c1f2e10e376e|title=Lilly Singh gets role in HBO reworking of Ray Bradbury's 'Fahrenheit 451'|last=Friend|first=David|date=June 19, 2017|website=National Post/The Canadian Press|access-date=June 27, 2017}}</ref> She plays the character of Raven, \"a tabloid blogger who works with the fire department to spread the ministry's propaganda by broadcasting their book-burning raids to fans\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/fahrenheit-451-movie-hbo-lilly-singh-1202469214/|title='Fahrenheit 451' HBO Movie Casts Digital Star Lilly Singh|last=Wagmeister|first=Elizabeth|date=June 16, 2017|work=Variety|access-date=June 27, 2017|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2017, Lilly Singh was also chosen as an ambassador for [[Pantene]] shampoo<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/lifestyle/vlogger-lilly-singh-now-pantene-ambassador-lifetime-growing-hair-finally-paid-off-174629771.html|title=Vlogger Lilly Singh is now a Pantene Ambassador: \"A lifetime of growing my hair has finally paid off\"|last=Prinzivalli|first=Leah|date=November 13, 2017|website=Yahoo|accessdate=January 13, 2018}}</ref> and partnered with [[Calvin Klein (company)|Calvin Klein]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/calvin-klein-amazon-fashion-pop-up-shop|title=There Are No Price Tags at Calvin Klein's Holiday Pop-Up|last1=Yotka|first1=Steff|date=November 16, 2017|work=Vogue|accessdate=January 13, 2018}}</ref> In 2018, Singh appeared in the music video for [[Maroon 5]]'s \"[[Girls Like You]]\" featuring [[Cardi B]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/maroon-5s-girls-like-you-video-featuring-strong-inspirational-women-is-just-what-we-needed/articleshow/64423895.cms|title=Gal Gadot, Ellen DeGeneres thank Maroon 5 for 'Girls Like You' video featuring strong, inspirational women|date=June 2, 2018|work=The Economic Times|accessdate=February 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===''A Little Late with Lilly Singh'' (2019\u2013present)===\nIn March 2019, [[NBC]] announced that Singh would host a new [[late night talk show]], ''[[A Little Late with Lilly Singh]]'', which succeeded ''[[Last Call with Carson Daly]]'' following its series finale later in the year.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/last-call-carson-daly-ending-17-years-nbc-1185796|title='Last Call With Carson Daly' Ending After 17 Years on NBC|first=Rick|last=Porter|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=February 12, 2019|accessdate=February 12, 2019}}</ref> The show premiered on September 16, 2019 to positive reviews by critics.<ref>{{Citation|title=A Little Late With Lilly Singh: Season 1|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/a_little_late_with_lilly_singh/s01|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n\nSingh garnered controversy for her remarks on [[turban]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2019/10/lilly-singh-little-late-night-show-review/599485/|title=Lilly Singh\u2019s Late-Night Challenge|last=Li|first=Shirley|website=[[The Atlantic]]|date=October 5, 2019|accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Controversy\">{{cite web|url=https://nextshark.com/lilly-singh-turban-joke/|title=Lilly Singh Made a Turban Joke on Her Late Night Show and People Aren\u2019t Happy|last=Ke|first=Bryan|website=NextShark|date=September 30, 2019|accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://asamnews.com/2019/09/29/late-night-host-lilly-singh-apologizes-for-turban-joke/|title=Late night host Lilly Singh apologizes for turban joke|last=Le|first=Brittney|website=AsAm News|date=September 29, 2019|accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref> During a visit to [[Jessica Alba]]'s home, Singh met Alba's two young daughters who were both wearing twisted towels on their heads, to which Singh responded \"They look like my [[Punjabi people|Punjabi]] friends [...]\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/tv/lilly-singh-apologizes-for-disrespectful-turban-joke-jessica-alba/|title=Youtuber Lilly Singh Apologizes for 'Disrespectful' Turban Joke She Made at Jessica Alba's Home|last=Dugan|first=Christina|website=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=September 30, 2019|accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref> On September 27, 2019, ''[[BBC]]'' reported that Singh had apologised for an on-air joke that compared turbans to bath towels, in which members of the [[Sikh religion]], who wear turbans for spiritual reasons, were angered by her remarks on NBC,<ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-49857361|title=Comedian Lilly Singh apologises for turban joke|last=BBC Editors|first=|website=[[BBC]]|date=September 27, 2019|accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref> with the ''BBC'' remarking that \"[Singh] has used her platform to often call out public figures who she says deserve to be \"cancelled\" for their offences.\"<ref name=BBC/>\n\nSingh was nominated for \"Audience Choice Creator of the Year\" at the [[9th Streamy Awards]]. She also was placed on Time's 100 Next, a list highlighting rising stars in different industries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://time.com/collection/time-100-next-2019/5718872/lilly-singh/|title=TIME 100 Next 2019: Lilly Singh|website=Time|language=en-us|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nSingh developed a strong connection with her [[Punjabi culture|Punjabi heritage]] during visits to India.<ref name=\"chick\">{{cite web|url=https://in.news.yahoo.com/the-chic-sikh-chick.html|title=The chic Sikh chick|last=Talwar|first=lolzersVidushi|date=June 25, 2012|publisher=[[Yahoo!]]|accessdate=July 2, 2014}}</ref> She struggled with depression, and began making YouTube videos as a way of dealing with her feelings.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/article/lilly-singh-youtube-depression|title=Lilly Singh: How battling Depression Turned YouTuber Lilly Singh Into a Superstar|date=November 13, 2015|website=People.com|publisher=Time Inc.|accessdate=December 15, 2015}}</ref> As a young adult, she lived with her parents in [[Markham, Ontario]]. In February 2019, Singh [[coming out|came out]] as [[bisexual]] to the public via social media.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/digital/news/lilly-singh-bisexual-youtube-1203148535/|title=YouTube Star Lilly Singh Comes Out as Bisexual, Gets Outpouring of Support|last=Spangler|first=Todd|date=2019-02-25|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n\n=== Philanthropy ===\nIn 2017, Lilly Singh was announced as a [[List of UNICEF Goodwill Ambassadors|UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador]], to advocate for children's rights. She has led a campaign called \"GirlLove\", promoting girls to end girl-on-girl bullying.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.unicef.org/media/media_96640.html|title=UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador|work=UNICEF Press Release|access-date=July 21, 2017|language=en}}</ref> In July 2018, Lilly traveled to South Africa as a UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador to meet the students of elementary schools who spoke against bullying and classroom violence.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.looktothestars.org/news/18149-lilly-singh-visits-south-africa-to-meet-students-affected-by-violence-in-school|title=Lilly Singh Visits South Africa To Meet Students Affected By Violence In School|date=July 26, 2018|work=Look to the Stars|access-date=August 7, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Comedic style ==\nPunjabi culture is frequently portrayed in her videos, which contain satires on people's complaints and prominent issues.<ref name=\"tina\">{{cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/mumbai/report-youtube-star-lilly-singh-aka-superwoman-the-tina-fey-of-punjabis-1965763|title=YouTube star Lilly Singh aka 'Superwoman' \u2013 The Tina Fey of Punjabis|last=Borges|first=Andre|date=February 28, 2014|work=[[Daily News and Analysis]]|accessdate=July 2, 2014}}</ref> Her most popular video is ''What Clubbing Is Actually Like (ft. Liza Koshy)'' and her most popular series features her fictional parents, Paramjeet and Manjeet, both played by Singh herself, reacting to trending and controversial videos.<ref name=\"tina\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2013/11/22/lilly-singh-superwoman-youtube_n_4324905.html|title=Lilly Singh Superwoman: YouTube Comedians Take on White people and Indian music is hilarious|last=Patel|first=Arti|date=November 22, 2013|work=The Huffington Post|accessdate=July 2, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/lilly-singh-is-youtubes-superwoman-20140530-zrtag.html|title=Lilly Singh is YouTube's Superwoman|last=Cormack|first=Lucy|date=May 30, 2014|work=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]|accessdate=July 2, 2014}}</ref> She also frequently collaborates with celebrities on her videos.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2016/07/lilly-singh-internet-firsts|title=Superwoman on the Rise: Meet Lilly Singh|last=Bradley|first=Laura|date=July 11, 2016|work=HWD|access-date=November 5, 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n===Allegations of cultural appropriation===\nSingh has also been accused of [[Cultural appropriation#African-American culture|cultural appropriation of African-American culture]], from such publications as ''[[The Huffington Post]]'', ''[[Bitch (magazine)|Bitch]]'', ''[[ColorLines]]'', and ''[[Vice (website)|Vice]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/non-black-minorities-appropriation_us_5d974be7e4b0f5bf797372ba|title=When Non-Black Minorities Adopt Black Style, Is It Still Appropriation?|last=Lambert|first=Bianca|website=[[The Huffington Post]]|date=October 14, 2019|accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bitchmedia.org/article/feminist-review-a-little-late-with-lilly-singh|title=\"A Little Late with Lilly Singh\" Has a Code-switching Problem|last=Koehler|first=Sezin|website=[[Bitch (magazine)|Bitch]]|date=October 21, 2019|accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_ca/article/7x5mmq/drake-torontos-slang-isnt-new-its-black|title=Toronto\u2019s Slang Isn\u2019t \u2018New.\u2019 It\u2019s Black|last=Taylor|first=Sharine|website=[[Vice (website)|Vice]]|date=October 21, 2019|accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://racebaitr.com/2019/05/08/taylor-swift-mocks-beyonce/|title=Taylor Swift isn\u2019t copying Beyonc\u00e9. She\u2019s mocking her.|last=Burton|first=Nylah|website=RaceBaitr|date=May 8, 2019|accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.colorlines.com/articles/performing-blackness-wont-fill-our-asian-american-culture-deficit-op-ed|title=Performing Blackness Won't Fill Our Asian-American Culture Deficit [OP-ED]|last=M Zhang|first=Muqing|date=August 22, 2019|website=[[ColorLines]]|accessdate=February 5, 2020}}</ref> Anna Silman of ''[[New York (magazine)|The Cut]]'' accused Singh of appropriating both black and Indo-Caribbean culture on her channel because of her tendency to don a \"[[blaccent]]\", whilst making rap videos sporting chains and [[cornrows]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thecut.com/2019/11/lilly-singh-vs-the-late-night-jimmys.html|title=Lilly Singh vs. the Late-Night Jimmys In a world of suits and cynicism, is there room for the YouTuber\u2019s rainbow unicorn vibes?|last=Silman|first=Anna|website=[[New York (magazine)|The Cut]]|date=November 1, 2019|accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref> Tayo Bero of ''[[Teen Vogue]]'' wrote that \"[Singh] falls into a category of non-Black people of color in entertainment who have built massive followings often by mimicking Black culture and leaning heavily into Black stereotypes.\"<ref name=\"Appropriation\">{{cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/lilly-singhs-late-night-show|title=Lilly Singh's Late-Night Show Is No Victory for All Women of Color|last=Bero|first=Tayo|date=September 27, 2019|website=[[Teen Vogue]]|accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref> Rachna Raj Kaur and Radheyan Simonpillai of ''[[Now (newspaper)|Now]]'' similarly criticized Singh's appropriation of Black culture due to her use of  braids, hip-hop slang and Caribbean accents.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://nowtoronto.com/movies/features/lilly-singh-nbc-late-night-talk-show/|title=NBC is playing it safe with Lilly Singh|last=Raj Kaur|first=Rachna|website=[[Now (newspaper)|Now]]|date=March 25, 2019|accessdate=January 23, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nowtoronto.com/movies/features/lilly-singh-interview-nbc-late-night/|title=Lilly Singh talks late-night, Trump and cultural appropriation|last=Simonpillai|first=Radheyan|website=[[Now (newspaper)|Now]]|date=September 9, 2019|accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref> Singh has responded to the criticism, by stating her mannerisms are due to her upbringing, adding \"all my friends from Scarborough act exactly like me.\u201d<ref name=\"Rachna\">{{cite web|url=https://nowtoronto.com/movies/features/lilly-singh-nbc-late-night-talk-show/|title=NBC is playing it safe with Lilly Singh|last=Raj Kaur|first=Rachna|date=March 25, 2019|website=[[Now (newspaper)|Now]]|accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2014\n| ''[[Gulaab Gang]]''\n| Herself\n| Playback singer and in song \"Mauj Ki Malharein\"\n|-\n| ''[[Dr. Cabbie]]''\n| Lilly\n| Guest appearance\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2016\n| ''[[A Trip to Unicorn Island]]''\n| Herself\n| Documentary; also executive producer\n|-\n| ''[[Ice Age: Collision Course]]''\n| Misty / Bubbles (voice)\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Bad Moms]]''\n| Cathy\n| <ref>{{cite news |last1=Spangler |first1=Todd  |title=YouTube Star Lilly Singh Comes Out as Bisexual, Gets Outpouring of Support |url=https://variety.com/2019/digital/news/lilly-singh-bisexual-youtube-1203148535/ |accessdate=February 28, 2019 |work=Variety |date=February 25, 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[F the Prom]]''\n| Miss Fallsburg\n| Cameo<ref>{{Citation|last=Fine|first=Benny|title=F*&% the Prom|date=December 5, 2017|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5612742/|others=Danielle Campbell, Joel Courtney, Cameron Palatas|accessdate=December 26, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Brooklyn Nine-Nine]]''\n| Dancer\n| Episode: \"Halloween II\". Lilly Singh played as one of the dancer from Gina's \"Floor-Gasm\" dance group.\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Bizaardvark]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"[[Bizaardvark#ep19|Paige's Birthday Is Gonna Be Great]]\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvlistings.zap2it.com/tv/bizaardvark-paiges-birthday-is-gonna-be-great/EP024192420019?aid=zap2it|title=Bizaardvark: Paige's Birthday Is Gonna Be Great|work=Zap2it|accessdate=December 12, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Fahrenheit 451 (2018 film)|Fahrenheit 451]]''\n| Raven\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2019\u2013\n| ''[[A Little Late with Lilly Singh]]''\n| Herself\n| Talk show\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2020\n| ''[[Medical Police]]''\n| Baroness Von Eaglesburg\n| Episode: \"Real Heavy Hitter\"\n|-\n| ''[[One World: Together at Home]]'' \n| Herself \n| Television special\n|-\n| ''[[The Simpsons]]''\n| Kensey (voice)\n| Episode: \"The Hateful Eight-Year-Olds\"\n|-\n|}\n\n===Web===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|-\n|2014\n| ''Giving Back Glam''\n|Host\n|11 episodes\n|-\n| 2014\n|''The Tube's Hautest''\n|Herself/ Various Characters \n|22 episodes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2015\n| ''Lana Steele: Makeup Spy''\n| Lana Steele\n| 12 episodes\n|-\n| ''[[Terminator Genisys#Marketing|Terminator Genisys: The YouTube Chronicles]]''\n| Lilly\n| Episode: \"Part Three\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gsb-8fsQ04U&list=PLZLTS4u9M_2rIL6wRYh9RxVAR5hd7SF_4&index=3|title=Terminator Genisys: The YouTube Chronicles Part 3|publisher=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=October 27, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Epic Rap Battles of History]]''\n| [[Wonder Woman]]\n| Episode: \"Wonder Woman vs Stevie Wonder\"\n|-\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Artist(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Role\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}} \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2017\n| \"Hold My Heart\"\n| [[Lindsey Stirling]] featuring Phelba\n| Herself\n|\n|-\n| \"H.A.I.R.\"\n| Humble the Poet\n| Herself\n|\n|-\n| 2018\n| \"[[Girls Like You (